The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Durgapur, March 31: Four executives were rescued by police around 9 this morning after being held hostage by workers for over 23 hours.

 The workers of Durgapur Cement Works had gheraoed the four yesterday, demanding a job for the kin of a deceased colleague.

 Mumbai (PTI): A cycling expedition to promote peace with Pakistan has hit a roadblock with the nine members of the team from Panvel in Maharashtra stuck in Amritsar, awaiting visas to cross the border.

 New Delhi (PTI): Rajeev Chawla, secretary to the Karnataka government, and R.S. Pandey, secretary in the ministry of steel, have been selected for the first Prime Ministers awards for excellence in public administration for 2005-06.




